description:
The invading armies of Napoleon Bonaparte had brought war to almost every country in Europe, and even into Egypt. Now they were marching into Russia with Moscow in their sights.

One of the officers in their ranks had first seen action thousands of miles to the east in Portugal. Then he had worn a different uniform... a British one. So what was he doing in the French column? Was he a traitor... or was he still serving king and country?
name: Deadly Deception

description:
By early 1945, Berlin - the once-proud capital of Hitler's Reich - lay in ruins, with Soviet forces poised to take control.

Wehrmacht Sergeant Jurgen Becker and his squad didn't hold out much hope for survival, until an officer offered them one last chance to escape the devastated city.

But their final mission involved the delivery of a hated Nazi officer into American hands, and a treacherous journey through the lines.
name: Through the Lines

description: An air ambulance Dakota filled with wounded troops, one of them a Jap officer. But the prisoner wasn't as badly hurt as he pretended, and now he was about to produce a live grenade high above the trackless wastes of the Burmese jungle!
name: Burma Hijack

description:
Theo Regens had a deep secret hate that festered within him. As the skipper of a stamp steamer in the war-torn Indian Ocean, it affected everyone he came in contact with, especially the Royal Navy demolition team he was transporting to the Jap-held port of Rujangi.

For Theo was on a one-man vengeance raid and his mission didn't coincide with that of the Navy.
name: Raid on Rujangi

description:
The Royal Artillery provide a constant barrage of heavy shellfire as support to British Infantry troops as they steadily advance through occupied Italy in 1943.

There's a friendly rivalry between them - the footsloggers think that all those Artillery lads do is fire their guns in the morning, then settle down to relax for the rest of the day.

But after a horrific accident in the field, Artillery Sergeant Henry Warburton is very badly shaken. It makes him wonder... is there such a thing in warfare as friendly fire?
name: Friendly Fire?

description: Alvin and his brothers start off in their first issue, trying to rock out and also please their adopted father Dave. Also has a few short Richie Rich stories
name: 1st spectacular issue!

description:
It had been the dream of Royal Air Force pilot Alan Lothian for as long as he could remember to circle the earth in a speeding spacecraft. That had come true for him when he found himself assigned to a Shuttle flight, with all the nerve and skill that required.

Coming back down to earth had its own dangers, and he and the crew were to find that out all too quickly when they landed in the middle of a civil war!
name: Shuttle Down

description:
For everybody else, it seemed the war in Europe had come to an end, but it was still business as usual for Ramsey's Raiders. They had a notorious Nazi to hunt down, and that could prove to be very dangerous indeed.

There was also the problem of Fitz who had gone absent without leave after thumping an officer. He was out there somewhere, and the rest of the raiding team wanted to know what he was up to....
name: The Final Raid

description:
Engineers, artillery, transport - all essential to any army at war. But when it comes to the crunch, it is the infantry - the footlsoggers - who have the most testing task of all.

For they are the men who decide the outcome of any battle... they are the men who must fight the enemy face to face...
name: The Foot Sloggers

description:
A demolition expert, a Red Army soldier, a Russian partisan, a Wehrmacht sapper and a member of a British bomb disposal squad. Sounds like quite a crowd, doesn't it?

But, in fact, they were all one man, a man called Ivan. And this is his story...
name: Ivan's War

description:
They were an odd bunch - a German soldier and an airman, together with a Russian from the German labour force. Put under the command of a short-sighted British pay clerk corporal named Henry Loftus, they were given the dangerous task of clearing the explosive left-overs of the recently ended war.

And no one was more surprised than Henry at just how good a team they proved to be, this squad called the bomb gang.
name: The Bomb Gang

description:
Ironbottom Sound - a name feared by sailors in the South Pacific. Old salts claimed it was called this because of the number of ships sunk there in that hostile stretch of water close to the Solomon Islands. This was long before the Japs arrived in 1942, when even more than ships were to perish.

But one Catalina flying boat crew from the Royal Australian Air Force was determined to salvage something from those dangerous waters - to help their American allies drive back the fierce invaders.
name: Sound of Death

description: The chipmunks are playing pirates! Join them in this exciting adventure where Chipmunks find a boat load of fun.
name: Alvin the ex-chipmunk

description:
When computer game designer Robert MacDowell, got the idea for a new project based on his grandfather's exploits in the Second World War, he had no idea what lay in store for him.

He planned to make the game as accurate and realistic as possible, but to his surprise - and horror - he found himself acting out his grandfather's last hours on a daring Commando raid into enemy territory!
name: War Game!

description:
The war in Europe was over, but for Captain Jimmy Ramsey and his Raiders the fighting went on. There were plenty of German troops willing to surrender - but there were also fanatical Nazis hiding out, and they had to be rounded up before they could escape.

The Raiders' difficult task was made even harder when they were saddled with an incompetent officer who caused chaos and threatened the team's very existence!
name: Raiders' Round-Up!

description:
Stalingrad, 1943.

The Nazis were surrounded by the Russians in a ring of fury that eventually led to the destruction of an entire German army.

And among the Germans tehre was a young officer who had a story linking him to another ring...a piece of jewellery which would span two world wars and lead to a deadly duel to the death!
name: Ring of Fury

description:
The Germans were on the run in late 1944 and were being pushed back into their homeland. But American rookie, Frank Pyle, was one of the first soldiers to realise that the enemy had hit back in the Ardennes sector and was planning to break out from their defensive positions to strike the Allies hard.

The trouble was... his superiors wouldn't believe him about this last-ditch breakout and that could alter the outcome of the war.
name: The Breakout!

description:
It started off as a German weapon, a boat that could rise above the water and fight at high speed... a military hydrofoil in other words. But then the British got their hands on the plans for these H-boats and came up with their own version which would soon wreak havoc in the Far East against the all-powerful Japanese.

That didn't please the enemy out East and they too built what they called ski-boats. A frantic fight to the finish was about to begin with a lethal top-secret weapon as the prize!
name: H-Boat Heroes

description: Simon builds a machine that will make people smarter. Alvin decides to use it to make himself smarter in school. WIll this make Simon loose his popularity in school? Will Alvin ever be the same? All questions will be answered in this issue.
name: The amazing talking cap!

description:
Bullying Nazi officer, ruthless killer. That was Hans Bayer. Of one thing he was sure in his arrogance... Germany would win the Second World War and eventually rule the world. He didn't give much thought to anything else, and he certainly didn't believe in ghosts.

Well, it seemed all that was about to change. It seemed that a phantom from his past, a captured British officer he had cold-bloodedly murdered during the First World War, had returned to haunt him...
name: Haunted By Fear

description:
Just what was going on at Torshelm Castle in Denmark in 1945 - or rather, in the heavily-guarded chamber underneath it? The Nazi occupiers were up to something which had the Allied top brass really worried, and Lieutenant-Colonel Nick Berry was given the job of going in and sorting it out.

So began one of the strangest operations of the Second World War... using a special ferry, a couple of armoured trains, a unit of very brave men, and a mysterious, young scientist.
name: Chamber of Horrors

description:
The air raid sirens had wailed all over Europe and parts of Asia since the start of the Second World War. They sent soldiers and civilians alike scurrying for cover as the dreaded bombers with their lethal loads droned closer.

But it wasn't seen as a threat across the wide Atlantic for the United States and for Canada. They were well beyond the range of any German bombers. Or, at least, they had been, until revolutionary new aircraft took to the skies with a very devastating mission in mind!
name: Air Raid!

description:
It was just a cheap six-dollar pocket watch, but it had been in the Cater family since the 1800s. Passed down from generation to generation, it had survived the American Civil War, the Indian Wars of the Wild West, and the blood-soaked trenches of World War One. So Frank Cater was devastated when he was taken prisoner in 1943 and the watch was looted by a German soldier.

But time has a way of playing funny tricks. The watch changed owners many times and where it ended up - well, you'll just have to read on to find out!
name: The War Watch

description:
Pirates... you usually expect to find them on the high seas, centuries ago, cutlasses at the ready, swinging from one ship to another and causing murder and mayhem.

But now meet another breed of pirates... speeding across desert dunes in make-shift sand yachts in the days of the Second World War. And this bunch was capable of causing even more grief to their enemy than any pirates who had ever sailed the oceans of the world!
name: Desert Pirates

description:
By early 1945, the fighting on the Western Front was mostly taking place on German soil as the Nazis were pushed further back by a determined Allied onslaught. Needless to say, Captain Jimmy Ramsey and his Raiders played a major part in this advance, scouting ahead of the main force and destroying any enemy positions they came across.

But operating deep inside Hitler's Reich was fraught with danger. And when faced by a larger and fanatical SS unit, and without any immediate Allied support, the Raiders had to rely on some very unlikely reinforcements if they were to win the day!
name: Raiders in the Reich
